April 15 (Reuters) -  U.S. stock indexes were lower on Tuesday. The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> was down 0.26 percent at 16,130.98, the S&P 500 <.SPX> was down 0.30 percent at 1,825.14 and the Nasdaq Composite <.IXIC> was down 1.04 percent at 3,980.868. [.N]

** THE COCA-COLA CO <KO.N>, $40.12, +3.59 pct The beverage giant reported better-than-expected quarterly revenue as strong sales in China more than offset a drop in Europe and flat volumes in North America. [ID:nL3N0N72YU]  ** PEP BOYS-MANNY, MOE & JACK <PBY.N>, $10.15, -15.20 pct The auto parts retailer reported a 7 percent drop in fourth-quarter revenue and said weak pricing is expected to hit results in the next quarter as well. [ID:nBw6zMDXda]  ** PERMA-FIX ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES INC <PESI.O> $4.26, -13.77 pct The provider of nuclear and mixed-waste management services reported a surprise fourth-quarter loss due to delayed government spending. [ID:nMKW2w733a]  ** INFOSYS LTD <INFY.N>, $50.95, -8.33 pct Staff left India's second largest IT services exporter at an unprecedented pace in the last quarter, worrying its management and raising investors' concerns about its ability to win lucrative contracts even as it posted a higher-than-expected net profit for the period. [ID:nL3N0N70T7]  ** AARON'S INC <AAN.N>, $28.56, -6.27 pct The rent-to-own furniture and electronics retailer rejected a $2.3 billion takeover offer from a major shareholder and instead acquired a retail credit financing firm for about $700 million. [ID:nL3N0N72SW]  ** NEWMONT MINING CORP <NEM.N>, $23.57, -3.44 pct ** AURICO GOLD INC, <AUQ.N>, $4.27, -2.73 pct ** ANGLOGOLD ASHANTI LTD <AU.N>, $17.44, -3.96 pct ** MCEWEN MINING INC <MUX.N>, $2.32, -2.52 pct ** GOLDCORP INC <GG.N>, $23.68, -2.35 pct ** ROYAL GOLD INC <RGLD.O>, $65.62, -3.03 pct ** IAMGOLD CORP <IAG.N>, $3.51, -3.31 pct ** ENDEAVOUR SILVER CORP <EXK.N>, $4.29, -2.94 pct Gold prices fell more than 2 percent on Tuesday as strength in the dollar following forecast-beating U.S. retail sales data pushed it through key chart levels while silver hit a 2-1/2 month low. Spot gold <XAU=> hit a low of $1,290.34 an ounce and was down 2.6 percent at $1,291.40 an ounce at 1246 GMT, on track for its biggest one-day drop since Oct. 1.  ** CHARLES SCHWAB CORP <SCHW.N>, $25.89, +2.33 pct The discount broker reported a higher-than-expected quarterly profit due to a rise in trading commissions and fees for managing client assets. [ID:nL3N0N73CC]  ** WALTER ENERGY INC <WLT.N>, $7.95, +1.92 pct ** ALPHA NATURAL RESOURCES INC <ANR.N>, $4.39, +1.15 pct Coal miner Walter Energy said it would idle its operations in Canada and temporarily lay off about 700 workers as it struggles with weak prices. [ID:nL3N0N73E0] The production cut also pushed up shares of rival Alpha Natural.  ** JOHNSON & JOHNSON <JNJ.N>, $98.52, +1.42 pct The diversified healthcare company reported quarterly earnings well above Wall Street expectations, as strong sales of new prescription drugs offset weak sales of consumer products, and slightly raised its full-year profit view. [ID:nL2N0N70FA]  ** RIVERBED TECHNOLOGY INC <RVBD.O>, $18.71, -0.80 pct Hedge fund Elliott Management reaffirmed its $3.36 billion offer for the network gear maker, saying it remained "extremely interested" in acquiring the company. [ID:nL3N0N73E6]  **  NATIONAL BANK OF GREECE SA <NBG.N>, $4.18, -6.28 pct Shares of Greece's biggest lender continued to fall on Tuesday after Reuters reported that it is moving ahead with plans for a share offering to bolster its capital. The bank must plug a 2.18 billion euro ($3.03 billion) capital shortfall under the terms of the country's international bailout, two senior bankers familiar with the issue told Reuters on Monday.[ID: nL6N0N61VF]  ** EAGLE BULK SHIPPING <EGLE.O>, $2.99, -5.97 pct A deadline for the drybulk shipper to reach an agreement to prevent a default on its $1.1 billion term loan ends Tuesday. Analysts say the company continues to face imminent Chapter 11 or restructuring risk.  ** FEDFIRST FINANCIAL CORP <FFCO.O>, $21.7, +8.17 pct CB Financial Services <CBFA.PK> said it would acquire Fedfirst Financial Corp in a $54.5 million deal. FedFirst stockholders can choose to receive $23 in cash or 1.1590 shares of CB common stock for each FedFirst share. [ID:nGNXVAHHFa]  ** MORGAN STANLEY <MS.N>, $29.05, -0.03 pct BofA Merrill Lynch upgraded Morgan Stanley to "Buy" from "Neutral", citing better returns and lower risk after a recent downturn in the bank's stock prices. BofA Merrill added that it expects Morgan Stanley's earnings to rise in wealth management, equities, and investment banking. The stock has fallen more than 10 percent since March 20.  ** HALOZYME THERAPEUTICS INC <HALO.O>, $7.33, +1.95 pct Analysts at Citigroup started coverage on the biotechnology company with a "buy" rating and a $12 price target, saying the commercial potential of its partnerships with Roche Holding AG <ROG.VX> and Baxter International Inc <BAX.N> were higher than consensus estimates and could speed up the progress of the company to profitability. Halozyme licensed its drug delivery technology to Roche and Baxter and is entitled to receive royalties and milestone payments on sales of products developed using the technology.   "We see substantial opportunity for these products, the cash flows of which should help support the development of Halozyme's proprietary pipeline," the analysts wrote in a note.  ** ZEBRA TECHNOLOGIES CORP <ZBRA.O>, $62.76, -8.08 pct ** MOTOROLA SOLUTIONS INC <MSI.N>, $62.97, -1.27 pct